fullDescription.markdown:
If resource `aws_s3_bucket` exists, then resource `aws_s3_bucket_server_side_encryption_configuration` must also exist with the key `apply_server_side_encryption_by_default`. Alternatively, the `aws_s3_bucket` resource should have the (deprecated) `server_side_encryption_configuration` key.

Vulnerable example #1 -
```
resource "aws_s3_bucket" "mybucket" {
  bucket = "mybucket"
}

# resource "aws_s3_bucket_server_side_encryption_configuration" is not defined
```

Secure example #1 -
```
resource "aws_s3_bucket" "mybucket" {
  bucket = "mybucket"
}

resource "aws_s3_bucket_server_side_encryption_configuration" "secure_example_1" {
  bucket = aws_s3_bucket.mybucket.bucket

  rule {
    apply_server_side_encryption_by_default {
      kms_master_key_id = aws_kms_key.mykey.arn
      sse_algorithm     = "aws:kms"
    }
  }
}
```

Vulnerable example #2 -
```
resource "aws_s3_bucket" "vulnerable_example_2" {
  # server_side_encryption_configuration is not set
}
```

Secure example #2 -
```
resource "aws_s3_bucket" "secure_example_2" {
  bucket = "mybucket"

  server_side_encryption_configuration {
    rule {
      apply_server_side_encryption_by_default {
        kms_master_key_id = aws_kms_key.mykey.arn
        sse_algorithm     = "aws:kms"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

